Hi Colin...sorry &#39;bout that.

Philip and I got sidetracked on other issues this
weekend...we didn&#39;t hash out changes to the network
XML.

I have uploaded what I&#39;ve currently got though. 
There&#39;s a zip file in the Files section of our group
called &quot;drawNetwork.zip&quot;.  It contains 4 files:

--network33.xml (a sample XML file)
--network33.svg (the SVG drawing of this network)
--draw.xsl (the style sheet that process the XML)
--draw.bat (a .bat file that contains the Xalan
processor command for converting the XML --&gt; SVG)

Here&#39;s what to do:
1) Unzip these files into the same directory
2) Make sure you have Xalan installed
(http://www.apache.org/dyn/closer.cgi/xml/xalan-j)
3) From a command line, type &quot;draw network33&quot;
4) Make sure you have an SVG viewer installed in your
browser
(http://www.adobe.com/svg/viewer/install/main.html)
5) Open network33.svg with your browser and there you
go!

Forward connections are in black, recurrent in red. 
Positive connection values are in black; negative are
in blue.  Notice that because this is *scalable*
vector graphics, you can right click on the image in
your browser and zoom in and out without loss of
resolution.

Now, this is the old form of XML, so we were still
explicitly placing neurons between layer tags, and
their position was determined by their order in the
XML.  And connections are always placed inside the
neuron tag for the neuron they are going *to*.  Here&#39;s
network33.xml:

