So if you want to use the style sheet as is, you&#39;ll
need to either generate your XML in this format or
write a style sheet to convert it into this format
(sorry!)...or, if you&#39;re skilled in XSL, you can try
to edit my style sheet (it&#39;s pretty ugly...I&#39;m no
expert in the technology).

Alternatively, you can send me or post a simple sample
of your XML and I can try to edit the XSL style sheet
based on your format.  If you do so, make sure the
network handles all possible types of connections
(forward, recurrent, and self).

